The paper discusses software engineering principles and techniques for developing scientific computing software, which suggests that it belongs to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of templates for Software Requirements and Module Interface Specification (MIS) suggests that it may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The focus on modelling a physical process (solidification of a metal alloy) suggests that it may belong to the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-category. The use of version control, issue tracking, and automation tools suggests that it may also belong to the Modeling and Simulation (cs.MS) sub-category. Finally, the emphasis on enabling replicability suggests that it may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
